The strongest issues are concentrated now: unchecked token-transfer assumptions, nominal-amount accounting that breaks on fee-on-transfer semantics, and a rebase path that is externally reenterable before `epoch.distribute` is refreshed. I’m tightening the exploit statements and severities so the JSON findings stay distinct and non-duplicative.
